      "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body": "There are only two signature encodings supported by this library: DER and compact.\r\n\r\nBitcoin's (deprecated) signmessage functionality takes a compact signature plus a recoveryid and encodes this in some weird 65-byte way by adding 27 to the recid or something like that. This library provides a bare minimum of support for this (having recoverable signatures, gated behind a feature flag, and exposing the recid as an integer with no prescribed encoding) because it's needed to compile Bitcoin Core, which is this library's primary target.\r\n\r\nThere are many reasons to dislike recoverable signatures and I don't expect this library will ever add additional support for them beyond this.",
