      "body": "I think we should support recoverable signatures, but we should do it in a way where R, S, and V are all explicitly specified as primitive values instead of any serialized \"representation\"\r\n\r\nThis allows a client to marshal them on their own because the client would have more knowledge than the library could ever.\r\n\r\nThis is why there's still tons of value in ECC functions taking primitive values, because its already been shown that there is variation in the serializing and encoding of these values.  I can re-work a patch-set / API to correctly take values in un-serialized form as well as a native implementation of key recovery (IIRC key recovery requires a value between 1-4 to know which of the four points +/- and P/P') to use for the computation of the ephemeral point for recovering the original signing point",
      "user": {
        "login": "rickmark",
        "id": 125403,
        "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEyNTQwMw==",
        "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/125403?v=4",
        "gravatar_id": "",
        "url": "https://api.github.com/users/rickmark",
        "html_url": "https://github.com/rickmark",
