      "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body": "@rickmark This library is focused on high-level functionality, exposing safe APIs ideally implementing specific protocols. It deliberately does not expose internals because (a) more risk of shooting yourself in the foot (b) they risk creating a dependency on internal representations which may change. There could be a discussion about changes to that, but this issue isn't the place for that.\r\n\r\nAs far as ECDSA recovery is concerned, I don't see what the outstanding issue to be addressed is here. The recovery module supports creating/serializing/deserializing/converting of signatures with recovery id. Recovery for normal ECDSA signatures isn't possible, as you'd need to guess the recid. I don't expect that we'll want to expand functionality around that.\r\n\r\nI'm going to close this due to unclarity about actionable improvements, but feel free to comment if you believe I missed something here.",
